        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.1",
          "pli": "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are these four bases of psychic power. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.2",
          "pli": "Katame cattāro? ",
          "en": "What four? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.3",
          "pli": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, ",
          "en": "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.4",
          "pli": "vīriyasamādhi … pe … ",
          "en": "energy … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.5",
          "pli": "cittasamādhi … ",
          "en": "mental development … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.6",
          "pli": "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—",
          "en": "inquiry, and active effort. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.7",
          "pli": "ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā. ",
          "en": "These are the four bases of psychic power. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.8",
          "pli": "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti. ",
          "en": "By developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.23:1.9",
          "pli": "Tatiyaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
